 Layer         Component                   Direction        Example                    
 Request Line  Method + URI + Version      Client → Server  `GET /index.html HTTP/1.1` 
 Headers       Host                        Client → Server  `Host: example.com`        
 Headers       User-Agent                  Client → Server  `User-Agent: Chrome/114`   
 Headers       Accept                      Client → Server  `Accept: text/html`        
 Headers       Connection                  Both directions  `Connection: keep-alive`   
 Headers       Server                      Server → Client  `Server: Apache`           
 Headers       Content-Type                Server → Client  `Content-Type: text/html`  
 Headers       Content-Length              Server → Client  `Content-Length: 1234`     
 Headers       Date                        Server → Client  `Date: Tue, 24 Jun 2025`   
 Status Line   Version + Code + Text       Server → Client  `HTTP/1.1 200 OK`          
 Body          Payload (HTML, JSON, etc.)  Server → Client  `<html>Hello</html>`       
 Body          Payload (if POST/PUT)       Client → Server  `{ "name": "John" }`       


